AGI - The agents of the 1st Historical Group of the Local Police of Rome Capital intervened in via Rasella, at number 3, to evacuate the Barberini > hotel for alleged toxic expositions: eight intoxicated persons are in need of medical care. On the fire station and staff of the local police, for the safety of the area and the viability of the area. Via delle Quattro Fontane was closed from Piazza Barberini to Via Rasella and via Rasella, from Via delle Quattro Fontane to Via del Boccaccio.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;According to what was reconstructed by firefighters, the exhalations would be traceable to the chlorine in the technical room at the service of the Spa on the lower floor of the hotel. All people within the structure were evacuated in order to allow more accurate control. They were also entrusted to 118 five people intoxicated by vapours for transport to the hospital. Further investigations are underway. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Five people have been transported to hospitals since 118, three of those with mild symptoms that would refuse transportation to the emergency room. Many of the guests of the hotel, > according to the AGI, would have reported that they had accused "burning in the eyes and shortness of breath" > in the moments after intoxication. &nbsp;

