AGI - Thirteen police officers were arrested for mistreatment and torture in the 'Beccaria' juvenile prison in Milan.>&nbsp; The State Police and the Regional Investigative Nucleus for the Lombardy of the Penitentiary Police have issued an order with which the detention in prison was placed against thirteen police officers, twelve of whom are still in service in the Penal Institute 'Cesare&nbsp;Beccaria' in Milan and the measure of suspension from the exercise of public offices against the same staff. The offences at various levels challenged by the Prosecutor of the Republic from at least 2022 to the present day and committed against several detainees of minor age, are those of mistreatment in damage of minors, also through omission, aggravated by the disabled defence and abuse of power; contest in the crime of torture, even through omission, aggravated by the abuse of power of the official public and by the fact of having committed the fact in harm of minors; contest in the offence of minor injuries, even through omission, aggravated by the abyss and futile motives, the disabled and the abuse of power; contest in the crime of false ideology and an attempted sexual violence of an agent against a prisoner.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Meeting journalists together with the pm Letizia Mannella and Rosaria&nbsp;Stagnaro, the prosecutor of Milan, Marcello Viola, > spoke of "a painful habitation and a bad page for the institutions. It's a press conference we never wanted to hold." The alleged victims of violence in the juvenile prison "would be handcuffed during the plagues. There was an office for pests in which these facts happened".&nbsp;Assaults would have occurred, sometimes even with sticks>, in some cells "defined by boys 'insulation' and without cameras", probably because they were involved in the renovation work lasted several months at the 'Beccaria'. "The handcuffs were put behind, so they couldn't use their hands to defend themselves. In some cases the signs on the face of violence were "extremely visible" were explained at the press conference. "As reported by the Prosecutor Letizia Mannella, the agents would have used to beat them on some occasions of the sand bags > not to leave trace of violence. "The climate was inevitable - he said -. The boys knew that at any time they could be beaten." The investigating agents are 21 out of about fifty. The Delinquer Association was not disputed. Prosecutor Viola said that "here to talk about an organization I'd be cautious" answering a question at the press conference. Mannella talked about "mele rotten." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> An inmate, "I lost blood and they continued to beat"></h2>
<br> "I lost blood from my mouth and nose > and in four they kept hitting me." One of the young presumed victims of plague and torture in the juvenile prison 'Cesare Beccaria' puts his story in record. The scenario is the office of the boss, without cameras. The boy's asking for a lighter to Agent Danilo who lets him out of the cell and takes him to the room where there are three other cops. "I don't know why she took it. After I said, "That's what, he slapped me, I didn't react, I just moved to not get my hands on me. After I moved it, they started to attack me all of them by filling me with kicks and fists, > throwing me on the ground with injuries here on my shoulder and I got up full of blood, that's where I lost blood, purple eye, drinking here, a little hurting the bones of the ribs, my back. Then they took me to the bathroom, they make me the son of a bitch, see you rinse because if not we give you more. Make a move. Now you don't have to break your dicks" &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2 The gip, "system of violence rooted in Beccaria"></h2>
&nbsp;
In the juvenile prison 'Beccaria' "there was a system of rooted violence". Stefania Donadeo writes this in the order of custody. "From the conversations emerges the total naturalness with which the custodian agents comment on the plagues and consequences of their actions on the minor prisoners - writes the judge -. All the tests analysed have allowed the existence of Cesare Beccaria of a consolidated system of repeated violence, harassment, bodily punishment, humiliation and group plagues carried out by the inquiries belonging to the prison police corps against minor prisoners." &nbsp;
<br A young prisoner in the prison 'Beccaria' would have been beaten by ten agents.' The fact would date back to 9 November 2023. In the order of precautionary custody it is read that an agent would spray him with pepper spray in his eyes, then others "were attacking him with kicks and fists all over the body and dropping him to the ground, as they insulted him saying 'You're a son of a bitch, your mother is a bitch, you're a clandestine, I'll show you how to make a son of a bitch'. "Once they lay on the ground - continues the reconstruction of the pollutants - handcuffed him, continuing to hit him and ripped his shirt, while the boy tried to defend himself with a piece of tile; after they led him to the first floor in a cell where they repeatedly hit him in the face and nose." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Trade union </h2>
&nbsp;
"Coworkers have made a mistake, their behaviors are absolutely to censor, and my conviction is without if and without but. In prisons, everything's happening, and the situation is from 'saving who can'. There are also other responsibilities: It is not justified that you only pay the prison police, someone in the judicial administration should be ashamed and resign." He tells the AGI&nbsp;Aldo Di Giacomo>, secretary of the Penitentiary Police Syndicate (SPP), commenting on the arrest of the 13 agents.
&nbsp;
"Sgoments and unbelievers." Thus Gennarino De Fazio, Secretary of the Uilpa Penitentiary Police, defines the state of mind after the news of the arrests. "Of course we have unconditional trust in the pollutants, including the Penitentiary Police itself, and in the judiciary and we hope that you will soon shed full light on the incident - he adds -. Nevertheless, we call for the presumption of innocence and hope in our heart that the agents involved can prove the correctness of their work." &nbsp;&nbsp; The secretary of Uilpa underlines that, regardless of the outcome of the investigation, "the conclaimed dysfunctionality" of the prison system "does not guarantee nor guards nor 'guards', and indeed inactivates consciences by generating and nourishing violence and atrocities sometimes from both sides of the infiriate". "Now we will listen to the usual speeches of politicians and then turn off the reflections - he continues -. Immediate reforms and a prison decree with urgent procedures to secure the system. Between suicides, 32 inmates and 4 in agents since the beginning of the year, murders and violence, you can't leave anymore. Minister Carlo Nordio and the President of the Council Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; at least this time they avoid catwalks and immediately open a serious confrontation, we are as always ready to offer our contribution of ideas".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
For the mayor of Milan, Giuseppe Sala, > "il&nbsp;Beccaria&nbsp; was abandoned for years and years, without a direction. So it's clear that certain things can happen. They can, but they shouldn't. We'll see what's coming out of this investigation."
